Make the field identifiers consistent with the UML and the rest of the code by using camelCase field names. For example, change the declarations to:
private String lectureName;
private int numberOfInscribedStudents;
private int numberOfGuestStudents;
private int numberOfLecturers;
private int numberOfTutors;
This aligns the declared fields with the constructor, getters/setters, the UML in the problem statement, and standard Java naming conventions. Alternatively, change all usages to match the declared snake_case names, but using camelCase is recommended.
